        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR3l0099-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:35:39.326+09:00">Shen Nung used his ochre flail to thresh the hundred plants.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:50:17.977+09:00">It was thus that he knew their natures entire -- whether normal, venomous, generating warmth or chill.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:38:45.476+09:00">Then, according to the class of their odor and taste,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:39:02.232+09:00">he sowed the hundred grains;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:39:36.387+09:00">this is why the world calls him the Farmer God.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:40:23.944+09:00">Ch'ih Sung-tzu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:40:40.267+09:00">was Rainmaster during the time of Shen Nung.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:41:38.419+09:00">He could go through fire and not be burned.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:42:55.624+09:00">When he reached the K'un-lun Range,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:43:29.977+09:00">he frequented the stone caves of the Queen Mother of the West.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:43:44.811+09:00">He could rise and sink with the rains and winds.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:44:11.242+09:00">The youngest daughter of Shen Nung followed him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:44:52.032+09:00">and also became transcendent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T01:45:34.663+09:00">They departed [the world] together.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:10:19.83+09:00">He swallowed ice and scattered jade,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:10:28.916+09:00">thereby to teach Shen Nung.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:11:14.452+09:00">At the time of Emperor Kao-hsin</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:11:33.252+09:00">he again became Rainmaster</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:11:51.465+09:00">and dwelt in the world of men.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:12:23.808+09:00">The Rainmaster of today began with him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:13:11.767+09:00">Ch'ih-chiang Tzu-lü, </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:13:34.159+09:00">lived during the age of the Yellow Emperor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:14:03.116+09:00">He abstained from the five grains,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:14:19.435+09:00">eating only the flowerings of herbs.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:14:31.815+09:00">During the time of Yao</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:14:45.081+09:00">he was the Timberworker</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:15:02.426+09:00">and could rise and sink with the winds and rain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:16:01.001+09:00">From time to time he would sell silk floss (?) at the market gate,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:16:19.462+09:00">wherefore he was called the Stringfather.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:16:45.752+09:00">Ning Feng-tzu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:16:57.432+09:00">lived in the days of the Yellow Emperor;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:17:26.834+09:00">common tradition has it that he was the Pottery Director of the Yellow Emperor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:17:53.552+09:00">Once, a person from distant lands came to him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:18:26.117+09:00">who could control [pottery] fire in his hands</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:18:54.318+09:00">and could come and (go) with the five-colored smoke.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:19:11.836+09:00">In time he taught this to Feng-tzu,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:19:35.517+09:00">who put the firewood together and set himself alight.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:19:59.809+09:00">He rose and fell with the smoke.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:20:15.376+09:00">When the fire-pan was inspected,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:20:34.805+09:00">it appeared that his bones were still there.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:21:17.004+09:00">The people of the time buried these remains on the north mountain of the Ning range.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:21:31.414+09:00">This is why he is called Feng-tzu of Ning.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:21:59.956+09:00">Wo Chü'an</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:22:19.883+09:00">was a herbalist on Mount Huai.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:22:46.266+09:00">He was given to eating the nuts of the pine.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:23:00.617+09:00">His entire body was covered with hair</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:23:15.392+09:00">seven inches long,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:23:30.396+09:00">and his pupils were exactly square.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:24:16.272+09:00">He could fly at the speed of a galloping horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:24:40.091+09:00">Once he presented his pine-nuts to Yao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:24:54.77+09:00">and Yao, without hesitation, ate them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:25:10.324+09:00">The seeds</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:25:34.138+09:00">were from the so-called simple pine (chien-sung)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:25:52.296+09:00">and people in those days who consumed such seeds</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-08T04:26:07.218+09:00">all lived to be 300 years old.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:46:47.839+09:00">P'eng Tsu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:47:19.718+09:00">was a Yin dynasty minister</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:47:27.827+09:00">whose surname was Ch'ien</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:47:38.396+09:00">and whose given name was Chien.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:47:54.845+09:00">He was the grandson of Emperor Chuan-hsü</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:48:15.889+09:00">and the middle child of the Lu-chung [Ends-of-the-earth] family.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:50:54.877+09:00">He lived during the Hsia and survived until the end of the Shang dynasty --</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:49:06.391+09:00">he is said to have been 700 years old.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:51:05.591+09:00">His regular food was the cinnamon fungus.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:51:31.402+09:00">In Li-yang there is a P'eng Tsu Sage Grotto,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:51:39.436+09:00">and in former times, they say,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:51:55.672+09:00">when one prayed there for wind and rain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:22:03.658+09:00">There used to be stone tigers on either side of the offertory.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:53:58.024+09:00">To this day there are still traces</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:54:10.668+09:00">of the two tigers to be found there.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T02:54:25.064+09:00">Shih-men</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:03:36.552+09:00">was a disciple of Hsiao-fu [The Whistler].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:03:42.055+09:00">He could manage fire</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:03:55.75+09:00">and ate only peach buds.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:04:10.196+09:00">He was Dragon Master for Emperor K'ung-chia,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:05:11.714+09:00">who could not identify with his ambitions,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:05:23.773+09:00">killed him, and buried him in the barren grounds.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:05:34.386+09:00">One dawn</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:05:46.206+09:00">great storms came upon him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:05:58.453+09:00">and all the mountain forests burst into flames.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:23:10.273+09:00">K'ung-chia erected an offertory to Shih-men and prayed,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-7a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:06:45.485+09:00">but he died before he could return home.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:07:05.743+09:00">Ko-yu of the early Chou</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:07:18.507+09:00">was a Ch'iang tribesman from Shu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:07:32.127+09:00">In the time of Chou Ch'eng-wang</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:20:06.166+09:00">he was given to carving wood rams and selling them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:07:57.578+09:00">One day,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:08:28.555+09:00">riding on his wooden ram he entered Mid-shu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:08:53.144+09:00">The King of Mid-shu, all his nobles, and men of consequence flocked to him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:09:03.669+09:00">and they all ascended Mount Sui.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:09:18.934+09:00">This mountain was covered with numerous peach trees;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:09:37.098+09:00">it lies to the southwest of O-mei Mountain</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:09:44.422+09:00">and reached boundlessly upward.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:20:26.58+09:00">None of those who followed Ko-yu returned to the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:10:16.916+09:00">for all reached sainthood.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:10:25.135+09:00">Wherefore the village saying goes:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:10:46.201+09:00">"From Mount Sui if you get a peach,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:11:28.649+09:00">Sagehood or power is in reach."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-8a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:13:19.681+09:00">Many shrines have been established at the foot of the mountain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:14:17.06+09:00">Ts'ui Wen-tzu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:14:33.872+09:00">was a man of T'ai-shan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:14:57.508+09:00">who studied for sagehood under Wang Tzu-ch'iao.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:15:23.245+09:00">Tzu-ch'iao transformed himself into a white rainbow-serpent</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:15:33.636+09:00">to carry the elixir to Wen-tzu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:25:37.708+09:00">The latter was amazed and frightened by the apparition,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:16:22.351+09:00">drew forth his dagger-axe and struck at the serpent,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:16:28.317+09:00">hitting it</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:16:37.241+09:00">and causing it to drop the elixir.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:25:18.302+09:00">When Wen-tzu bent down to look,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:25:43.263+09:00">he discovered the corpse of Wang Tzu-ch'iao.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:25:59.825+09:00">Tzu-ch'iao placed the body in a room</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:26:09.48+09:00">and covered it with an old basket.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:26:18.296+09:00">Later,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:26:34.757+09:00">the remains transformed into a great bird,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:26:49.913+09:00">and when Tzu-ch'iao lifted the basket to look,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-9a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:26:55.85+09:00">off it soared.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:27:36.975+09:00">Kuan Hsien</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:27:42.726+09:00">lived in Sung</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:27:50.855+09:00">and was a fisher by trade.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:28:08.029+09:00">He dwelt on the bank of the Sui River,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:28:16.552+09:00">and there he fished for over 100 years.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:28:25.349+09:00">Whenever he caught fish,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:19:31.521+09:00">he would either release,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:28:37.5+09:00">sell,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:28:49.633+09:00">or feed and raise them himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:29:07.853+09:00">He always wore a formal cap and sash.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:29:19.177+09:00">He loved to plant lichee trees</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:29:32.717+09:00">and to eat the flowers and fruit therefrom.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:30:04.159+09:00">Duke Ching of Sung asked him the secret methods of his Way,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:30:41.276+09:00">but Kuan Hsien would tell the Duke nothing,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:30:57.294+09:00">so the latter had him executed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:31:41.026+09:00">Several decades later</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:27:41.153+09:00">he was seen squatting atop the Sung city gate-house</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:38:16.738+09:00">strumming his ch'in zither.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:38:34.534+09:00">There he stayed for twenty or thirty days before he departed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-10a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:38:56.084+09:00">Every household in the city-state of Sung makes offerings to him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:39:02.853+09:00">Ch'in Kao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:39:10.749+09:00">a man of Chao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:39:18.264+09:00">was an accomplished ch'in player.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:49:49.869+09:00">He became a retainer for King K'ang of Chao</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:50:18.338+09:00">and practiced the arts of Chüan-tzu and P'eng Tsu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:50:40.201+09:00">He floated and wandered about Chi-chou and the Commandery of Cho for over a century</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:50:54.792+09:00">before he finally took his leave and plunged into the Cho River</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:51:02.068+09:00">to capture a young dragon.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:32:40.653+09:00">He covenanted with his disciples,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:51:30.565+09:00">saying:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:51:53.784+09:00">"On the morrow be clean and abstemious and await me."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:52:12.349+09:00">They set up an offertory at the riverbank,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:52:38.897+09:00">and at the appointed time Ch'in Kao came riding a great red carp.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:52:45.156+09:00">He sat in his offertory,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:53:05.01+09:00">and there must have been ten thousand who witnessed this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:53:14.434+09:00">He remained there for a month</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:54:06.505+09:00">T'ao An-kung</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:54:31.631+09:00">was the master smelter of Liu-an.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:55:08.125+09:00">A number of times he established his smelting fires;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:55:52.064+09:00">then one morning one of his smelters scattered and sprang up.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:56:22.86+09:00">From it there came a shaft of purple light that beat against the heavens.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:56:37.949+09:00">Discouraged, An-kung lay down beneath his smelter and prepared himself for death.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:59:31.796+09:00">Only a moment later</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:59:45.521+09:00">the Crimson Sparrow lit on the smelter</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T03:59:51.93+09:00">and spoke:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:00:04.195+09:00">"An-kung,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:00:10.405+09:00">An-kung!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:00:32.036+09:00">Light from your smelter reached to heaven today.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:00:39.674+09:00">On the Seventh of the Seventh</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:00:47.624+09:00">Red Dragon will carry you away!"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:01:50.268+09:00">When that day arrived,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:01:59.402+09:00">An-kung mounted the beast</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:02:40.138+09:00">and started off to the southeast.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:03:00.209+09:00">Tens of thousands of his fellow townsmen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:03:12.048+09:00">saw him off with sacrifices to speed him on his way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-12a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:03:29.319+09:00">He bade them all farewell.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:04:06.145+09:00">There was once a man who stayed in the Firewood Mountains for seven years.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:04:52.03+09:00">The Ancient Master [Lao-tzu] gave him a wooden awl</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:14:57.964+09:00">and set him to boring through an anchor stone</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:18:22.54+09:00">five feet thick.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:15:14.218+09:00">The ancient one told him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:15:23.258+09:00">"When you have bored through this stone,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:15:33.333+09:00">you will have attained the Tao."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:36:14.221+09:00">For forty years together he worked.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:15:51.587+09:00">The stone finally being pierced,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-13a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:16:00.312+09:00">he learned the alchemy of gods and sages.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:16:07.786+09:00">Lu Shao-ch'ien</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:16:17.207+09:00">came from Shan-yang.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:36:35.591+09:00">Emperor Wen of the Han once disguised himself and took a fortune in gold to Lu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:16:56.533+09:00">in the hope of learning his Way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:17:09.906+09:00">Shao-ch'ien, leaning on his gold staff</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:17:17.099+09:00">and holding a carved ivory fan,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-14a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:17:29.892+09:00">thrust the emperor out of his front door.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-11a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:18:50.466+09:00">and then returned to the river.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-31T04:22:00.917+09:00">the request was immediately granted.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-04T02:58:55.525+09:00">Even though we examine ancient fragments in the written documents</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-04T02:59:45.911+09:00">Even though we examine ancient fragments in the written documents</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-04T03:00:30.749+09:00">and collect bits and pieces which have come to the present time,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-04T03:00:57.14+09:00">these things are not what has been heard or seen by one person's own ears and eyes.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:38:45.11+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:38:34.284+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:42:15.832+09:00">then this point will surely seem a defect of previous historians.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:42:00.811+09:00">and only then regard them as veritable, </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:41:47.083+09:00">have words in every text agree </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:41:24.894+09:00">If one must have historical events without any discrepancies</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:42:44.326+09:00">Nevertheless the state does not eliminate the office charged with writing commentaries on historical documents</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:42:58.918+09:00">and scholars do not cease in their recitation of the texts</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:43:17.69+09:00">is it not because what is lost is inconsequential </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:43:20.74+09:00">and what is preserved is vital?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:43:27.924+09:00">As for what I am putting together now,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:43:36.61+09:00">when there are items gotten from previous accounts</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:43:45.976+09:00">the fault is not mine.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:44:17.559+09:00">In the event they are from recent happenings which I have collected or discovered,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:44:25.167+09:00">should there be any errors or omissions,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:45:48.498+09:00">the ridicule and condemnation with scholars and worthies of the past</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:45:50.683+09:00">I will hope to share (transposed translation).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:45:58.413+09:00">Coming now to what these records contain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:46:11.752+09:00">it is enough to make clear that the spirit world is not a lie.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:46:27.573+09:00">On this subject the countless words and the hundred different schools</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:46:45.158+09:00">are too much even to scan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:46:58.781+09:00">and what one perceives with one's own eyes and ears</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:47:07.265+09:00">is too much to write down</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:47:25.272+09:00">so I have lumped together records that are just adequate to express the main points of the eight categories,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:47:52.668+09:00">provide some trivial accounts. That is all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:48:13.72+09:00">I will count myself fortunate if in the future curious scholars come along</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:48:26.058+09:00">know the basis of these stories</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:48:36.738+09:00">and find things within them to enlighten their hearts</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:48:48.434+09:00">and fill their eyes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:49:07.804+09:00">and I will be fortunate as well to escape reproach for this book.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-04T04:53:00.134+09:00">How could one dare to say there are no inaccuracies?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T19:58:54.347+09:00">The Prince of Huai-nan, An,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T19:59:39.982+09:00">was very fond of Taoist arts,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T19:59:57.843+09:00">and he kept a chef-butcher always ready to entertain visitors who might teach him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:00:28.968+09:00">At noon of the first of the first month,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:00:58.197+09:00">eight elderly persons persented themselves at his gate wishing audience.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:01:22.445+09:00">The gatekeeper reported this to the Prince,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:01:58.713+09:00">who told him to deliberately twit them by</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:02:03.082+09:00">saying:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:02:23.947+09:00">"Our Prince is interested in the arts of longevity.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:02:50.645+09:00">You gentlemen do not seem to have prevented the decay of age,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:03:01.862+09:00">so he will not attend you."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:03:13.523+09:00">When they understood they would not be given audience,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:03:30.203+09:00">they changed themselves into eight young men</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:03:41.822+09:00">with peach-bloom complexions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:04:03.055+09:00">Thereupon the king immediately received them,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:04:16.05+09:00">entertained and feasted</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:04:28.868+09:00">the eight gentlemen with great courtesy.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:04:45.503+09:00">Seizing his ch'in, he played</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:04:52.943+09:00">and sang:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:05:18.367+09:00">"Becoming clear on clarity, You ascend the sky</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:05:31.112+09:00">Shining on the four seas, oh</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:05:38.229+09:00">Knowing I love the Tao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:05:48.836+09:00">My lords come down to me, oh.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:05:59.87+09:00">My lords will give to me</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:06:19.643+09:00">Wings and feathers, oh.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:06:29.871+09:00">That I might rise to the clouds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:06:42.949+09:00">Tread Mount Transcedent Bridge, oh,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:06:58.415+09:00">Witness the sun, the moon and stars</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:07:08.359+09:00">And come upon the Dipper, oh,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:07:27.08+09:00">Harness and drive the wind and cloud</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:07:34.308+09:00">To summon Jade Maiden, oh.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-15a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-10-14T20:07:58.913+09:00">This song is what we now call the Huai-nan Exercise.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
